<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cause-vt">cause <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kɔːz/    美 /kɔːz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>引起；导致</strong></h4>
<p>to make sth happen, especially sth bad：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Unpunctual people seldom realise that their habit causes problems to others. 
不守时的人很少会意识到他们的习惯给别人带来不便。</p><footer> 2015 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everyone believes that global warming is caused by human activities.
人们普遍认为全球变暖是由人类活动所导致的。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 4改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>cause sb sth / cause sth for sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His wound caused him great suffering. 
他的伤让他深受痛苦。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bad weather is causing problems for many farmers. 
坏天气给很多农民带来麻烦。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>cause sb / sth to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What caused you to change your mind? 
是什么让你改变了主意？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The heavy rain caused the river to rise. 
大雨引起河水上涨。</p></div></div>